videos.description: Trace McSorley throws a 48-yard strike to DaeSean Hamilton who evades a tackle for a touchdown on Penn State's first drive.
videos.headline: Penn State's Hamilton dodges tackles for opening TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley overthrows his receivers and Byron Murphy intercepts it in the end zone.
videos.headline: Washington's Murphy reels in toe-dragging interception

videos.description: Saquon Barkley finds a small hole for a 2-yard touchdown to give Penn State a two-touchdown lead in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Barkley leaps into the end zone for TD

videos.description: Washington throws a double pass to Will Dissly for a 52-yard catch-and-run to Penn State's 12-yard line.
videos.headline: Washington dials up trick play for 52-yard gain

videos.description: Jake Browning punches in a 1-yard touchdown on a quarterback keeper for the Huskies.
videos.headline: Browning keeps it himself for TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley throws a back-shoulder pass to DeAndre Thompkins for a 34-yard gain to the 1-yard line.
videos.headline: Penn State's Thompkins hauls in 34-yard pass

videos.description: Miles Sanders just gets into the end zone for a 1-yard touchdown as the Nittany Lions build a 21-7 lead.
videos.headline: Penn State's Sanders punches in short TD

videos.description: Miles Sander can't corral Trace McSorley's toss and Washington's Ryan Bowman pounces on the loose ball.
videos.headline: Miscommunication causes Penn State turnover

videos.description: Myles Gaskin takes the direct snap and runs up the middle for a 13-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Gaskin makes defender miss for TD

videos.description: Penn State's coach James Franklin isn't pleased with his team's first half despite their 28-14 halftime lead because of turnovers.
videos.headline: Franklin 'not happy' with first half

videos.description: The Nittany Lions erupt for 28 points in a strong first half against Washington.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Penn State's offense red-hot in first half) 2017/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Penn State's offense red-hot in first half

videos.description: Jake Browning's throwaway pass is caught by the Nittany Lion on the sidelines of the Fiesta Bowl.
videos.headline: Even Penn State's mascot is making plays

videos.description: Jake Browning throws a strike to Aaron Fuller for a 28-yard touchdown for the Huskies.
videos.headline: Washington's Fuller hauls in 28-yard TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley throws a deep ball to DaeSean Hamilton for a 24-yard touchdown, restoring Penn State's two-touchdown lead.
videos.headline: Penn State responds with 24-yard TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley's batted pass falls right into the hands of Washington's Austin Joyne.
videos.headline: Red-zone interception gives Huskies life

videos.description: Myles Gaskin takes the direct snap on the wildcat and runs straight through for a 69-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Gaskin gashes Penn State defense for 69-yard TD

videos.description: Tyler Davis kicks a 45-yard field goal wide right that would have given Penn State a two-possession lead.
videos.headline: Penn State's Travis misses 45-yard FG

videos.description: Washington attempts to score on a lateral play, but throws the ball right to Penn State's Brandon Smith.
videos.headline: PSU ices game on interception during failed lateral

videos.description: Penn State's coach James Franklin says he "couldn't be more proud" of his team after their 35-28 win over Washington in the Fiesta Bowl.
videos.headline: Franklin: 'It's just the beginning'

videos.description: Saquon Barkley thanks his teammates and says it's been an "honor" to call them his teammates and brothers, but he'll celebrate Saturday's bowl win and make a decision on the draft "when it hits me."
videos.headline: Barkley doesn't give decision on NFL draft

videos.description: Saquon Barkley rushes for 137 yards and two touchdowns while Trace McSorley adds 342 yards through the air and two TDs as well as Penn State holds on to beat Washington 35-28 in the PlayStation Fiesta Bowl.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Barkley, Penn State hold on for win against Washington) 2017/12/30 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: Barkley, Penn State hold on for win against Washington

videos.description: Penn State improves to 7-0 all-time in the Fiesta Bowl after defeating Washington 35-28.
videos.headline: PSU hoists 2017 Fiesta Bowl trophy

videos.description: Greg McElroy says Trace McSorley was "off the charts" and "poised" in Penn State's Fiesta Bowl win against Washington.
videos.headline: Trace McSorley helps Penn State knock off Washington

videos.description: No. 9 Penn State jumps out to a big lead behind a monster game from Saquon Barkley, but No. 11 Washington storms back before eventually falling 35-28 in the PlayStation Fiesta Bowl.
videos.headline: Penn State tops Washington in a thriller
